<font color="#FF0000">THE IMMORTAL 13</font><br>
<tt>Mon Oct  6 19:10:19 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Bob SW,<br><br>
Had to get out my State of Tennessee history book to find the Immortal Thirteen. They were Democratic obstructionists during the time of Jackson and Polk (both Tennesseans).<br><br>
I live a short distance from where Davy Crockett was born in Limestone, TN. Andrew Johnson, who succeeded Lincoln after his assassination, is from Greeneville - my adopted hometown.  There are several historic sites here that are maintained by the National Park Service. I have been fortunate enough to have done a good deal of restoration on these and many of the historic homes in this area. Greeneville is the second oldest town in Tennessee.<br><br>
When I moved here 25 years ago, people thought that it was nothing but backwoods hillbillys. Nothing could be further from the truth.<br><br>
As a friend of mine once put it: &quot;when people take it upon themselves to be neighborly, seeing after your crops if you are sick and helping with the chores and getting in the firewood - that is being CIVILISED. People from up north, who live in large cities and don't know their next door neighbors, are a far cry from being civilised. They know very little about taking care of one another.&quot;<br><br>
Some of the wisest people I ever have had the good fortune to meet could barely read or write. We hear the jokes about our state and its people, but the funny thing is when people come to visit they don't ever want to leave.
<p><code>-- wingman&amp;greene..xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


